{
  "_comment": "Unit type library. Values are simplified but grounded in open-source data. sensor_km = detection range, weapon_km = max engagement range, attack_per_tick = damage per 60s tick at full engagement, default_hp = starting health. fuel_burn_per_tick = % fuel consumed per tick when moving, fuel_idle_per_tick = % when stationary, rearm_ticks = ticks at home base to fully rearm & refuel. data_link = true means the unit participates in the tactical data network (Link-16/MADL/AFATDS/SEWACO) — data-linked units share their sensor picture so any data-linked friendly can engage targets detected by any other data-linked friendly. loadout_presets define magazine counts per ammo class: aa (anti-air), ag (anti-ground), as (anti-ship).",

